==English==
Jay-Kob. Simple you dimwits!

===Etymology===
From Late Latin [[Iacobus]] < Greek [[Ιάκωβος]] < Hebrew [[יעקב]] (''yaaqov'', heel-grabber) < [[עקב]] (''‘akev'', [[heel]] of the foot). Cognates include [[James]] and [[Jim]].

===Proper noun===
'''Jacob'''

#a male [[given name]].

